comments.body: This failed again https://app.circleci.com/pipelines/github/pulibrary/figgy/2802/workflows/fb67d514-06d6-43f5-a574-eff29f6283f4/jobs/33091
keep the source tiffs but hold off migrating to Figgy until a METS/ALTO strategy is developed.
I'm not sure. I think @jpstroop would know maybe? Most of these tickets were just migrated from the spreadsheet.

The Friends paid to have this digitized but wanted a JStor-like interface so we, erm, gave derivatives to JStor. These are the master archival files and we need to keep them because JStor, iirc, only has relatively small JPEGs and isn't really a repository.
(to answer @kelea99's question: they were never public anywhere else digitally)

Thanks, @jpstroop .  If our intent is to keep the entire digitized run eternally dark and have them in Figgy for preservation reasons alone, I wonder if Figgy is the right place for them. If it is, maybe  we should discuss adding a visibility indicator for such things that are to remain dark in Figgy (other than Private). @escowles I think the MVW ingest would work fine if we are only preserving them in Figgy.  If we want to make stuff available to users, the User Experience for the MVW in our catalog should probably be tested and discussed (think Trentonian). All of these appear to be open access on JSTOR, but if we decided to make the high resolution versions available at some point via figgy, the MVW access  is currently an all or nothing setting - they would all be open, or they would all be CDL (due to copyright) and physical items would need to be sequestered.

@kelea99 I think it's fine to ingest them as Private — corner cases like this are the main reason that Visibility and Rights are separate fields. And I agree that ingesting as one big MVW is fine for this purpose, but would be trouble if we wanted to make them accessible.
